### Features

These chart types are available for use.

 - `chart/bar`
 - `chart/bubble`
 - `chart/doughnut`
 - `chart/line`
 - `chart/pie`
 - `chart/polar-area`
 - `chart/radar`
 - `chart/scatter`

### Usage

~~~ .php
[
    'type' => 'chart',
    'state' => [
        'type' => 'line',
        'data' => [ … ],
        'options' => [ … ]
    ],
    'stack' => 10
]
~~~

State data is the same as the configuration data you will find in the documentation page of [Chart.js](https://www.chartjs.org/docs/latest)

You don’t need to declare the chart type back in the state data when using specific chart type names.

An example page to display the chart is available at the following [link](http://127.0.0.1/panel/::g::/.test/chart).
